@@ -3,5 +3,6 @@
 ## 2026-06-28
 
+- Added a Stocktwits RapidAPI fallback key setting and collector retry guard so fallback credentials are used only after the primary key fails through the configured retry window.
 - Hardened Document 2 runtime boundaries from the node contract matrix review: resolver deterministic revalidation now retains non-numeric blockers, promotion fail-closes with rejected audits for hidden deterministic issues, SYSTEM-authored Document2 promotion patches use a narrow submit permission, proposed_patches leaks and detail delegations are rejected, and final payload adaptation no longer invents semantic candidate fields.
 - Added a fast offline Document 2 fixture-driven node contract matrix covering construction, detail generation, field review, resolver, and promotion boundaries, plus a report of expected/questionable/bug/orchestration-error outcomes.
 - Expanded the Document 2 node contract matrix with mini-flow, deterministic revalidation, final-payload adapter, detail delegation, metadata sync, and finding-lifecycle fixture coverage; updated the matrix report with the new expected/questionable/bug/orchestration-error classifications.

